---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Crystal AI"
  description="How Crystal AI collects, uses, and protects information submitted through buildcrystal.ai."
  ogTitle="Privacy Policy"
  ogDescription="Plain-English privacy policy for buildcrystal.ai. No cookies, no analytics, no tracking."
>

  <section class="hero hero-slim">
    <div class="frame">
      <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-04-16</p>
      <p class="lede">
        This policy explains what information Crystal AI collects through buildcrystal.ai, how it
        is used, and what rights you have over it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="band band-paper">
    <div class="frame legal">

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Crystal AI is a trade name operated by KESA LLC, a single-member LLC organized under the
        laws of Minnesota, USA. Austin VanAlstyne is the sole operator. KESA LLC is the data
        controller responsible for information collected through this site.
      </p>
      <p>
        For privacy-related questions or requests, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:help@buildcrystal.ai">help@buildcrystal.ai</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What this policy covers</h2>
      <p>
        This policy applies to information collected through buildcrystal.ai and any forms hosted on
        that domain.
      </p>
      <p>
        It does not cover AI workers deployed on customer properties or third-party platforms. Those
        deployments are governed by separate agreements between Crystal AI and the applicable
        customer.
      </p>

      <h2>3. What we collect</h2>
      <p><strong>Contact form submissions.</strong> When you submit a form on this site, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name</li>
        <li>Your work email address</li>
        <li>Your business or company name</li>
        <li>Which role or worker you are inquiring about</li>
        <li>An optional free-text message (if you choose to include one)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You provide this information voluntarily. We do not collect it any other way.</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Server logs.</strong> Our hosting and content delivery network (CDN) provider
        automatically records standard server log data when you visit this site. This includes your
        IP address, browser user agent, referring URL, and the date and time of the request. We do
        not control this logging; it is a standard function of web hosting infrastructure. These
        logs are retained according to our hosting provider's policies.
      </p>

      <h2>4. What we don't collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No cookies &mdash; session, persistent, or otherwise</li>
        <li>No analytics (no Google Analytics, no Plausible, no PostHog, nothing)</li>
        <li>No tracking pixels or fingerprinting scripts</li>
        <li>No social login or account creation</li>
        <li>No payment information</li>
        <li>No third-party advertising scripts or embeds</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If you do not submit the contact form, we collect nothing beyond what the hosting provider
        logs automatically.
      </p>

      <h2>5. How we use your information</h2>
      <p>We use contact form submissions to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your inquiry</li>
        <li>Evaluate whether Crystal AI's services are a fit for your business</li>
        <li>
          Route your submission through our internal AI workers (Crystal Support Rep and Crystal
          Reception) for processing, intent classification, and response drafting
        </li>
        <li>Maintain a record of the interaction in our internal CRM (Notion)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use your information for unsolicited marketing. If you submit the form, we reply
        to you. That is the extent of it.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Who we share it with</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your data. We do not share it with advertisers. We share information only
        with the following service providers, who act as data processors on our behalf:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Anthropic.</strong> Form submissions, including any free-text message you provide,
        may be processed by Anthropic's API as part of our AI worker pipeline. Anthropic acts as a
        processor, not a controller. Anthropic does not train its models on data submitted via the
        API. Anthropic's privacy practices are described at
        <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy" rel="noopener">anthropic.com/privacy</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Notion.</strong> Submitted information is stored in our Notion workspace, which
        serves as our internal CRM and knowledge base. Notion acts as a processor. Notion's privacy
        practices are described at
        <a href="https://www.notion.so/privacy" rel="noopener">notion.so/privacy</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Hosting and CDN provider.</strong> Our site is served via a content delivery
        network. Server log data described in Section 3 is retained by that provider.
      </p>
      <p>We do not share your information with any other third parties.</p>

      <h2>7. How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>
        We retain inquiry records in Notion for as long as the business relationship or
        conversation is active.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you ask us to delete your information, we will do so. Send a deletion request to
        <a href="mailto:help@buildcrystal.ai">help@buildcrystal.ai</a>. We will confirm
        deletion within a reasonable time. Note that we cannot delete information already retained
        in third-party provider server logs, which are outside our control.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>For everyone.</strong> You can request access to the information we hold about
        you, ask us to correct inaccurate information, or ask us to delete your information. Email
        <a href="mailto:help@buildcrystal.ai">help@buildcrystal.ai</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>California residents (CCPA).</strong> You have the right to know what personal
        information we have collected about you and how it is used, to request deletion of your
        personal information, and to opt out of the sale of your personal information. We do not
        sell personal information. You will not be discriminated against for exercising any of
        these rights.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>EU and UK residents (GDPR / UK GDPR).</strong> You have the right to access your
        personal data, to correct inaccurate data, to request erasure, to request a portable copy
        of your data, and to object to processing. Because our lawful basis for processing your
        contact form submission is legitimate interest (responding to a business inquiry you
        initiated), you have the right to object. To exercise any of these rights, email
        <a href="mailto:help@buildcrystal.ai">help@buildcrystal.ai</a>. If you believe we
        have not handled your data lawfully, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your
        local supervisory authority.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are a small operation. We will handle rights requests manually and in good faith. We
        cannot guarantee automated fulfillment timelines, but we will respond.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This site and our services are not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from anyone under 13. If you believe a minor has submitted
        information through this site, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:help@buildcrystal.ai">help@buildcrystal.ai</a> and we will delete it.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable administrative and technical measures to protect the information you
        submit. Form submissions are transmitted over HTTPS. Access to our internal systems is
        restricted.
      </p>
      <p>
        No system is perfectly secure. We cannot guarantee that information will never be
        accessed, disclosed, or lost through circumstances outside our control. In the event of a
        material data breach affecting your information, we will notify you as required by
        applicable law.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        When we update this policy, we will change the "Last updated" date at the top. For
        material changes &mdash; meaning changes that meaningfully affect how we collect or use
        your information &mdash; we will post a notice on the buildcrystal.ai homepage for at
        least 30 days.
      </p>
      <p>
        Continued use of the site after a policy update constitutes acceptance of the revised
        policy.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, access requests, correction requests, or deletion requests:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong>
        <a href="mailto:help@buildcrystal.ai">help@buildcrystal.ai</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Mailing address:</strong><br />
        KESA LLC<br />
        200 4th Ave SW<br />
        Isanti, MN 55040
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .hero-slim {
    padding-top: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
    padding-bottom: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
  }
  .hero-slim .updated {
    margin: 0.4rem 0 1.25rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .legal {
    max-width: 44rem;
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 2.25rem 0 0.6rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .legal h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .legal p {
    margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .legal ul {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .legal ul li {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .legal a {
    color: var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 120ms ease, border-color 120ms ease;
  }
  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-ink);
    border-bottom-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .legal strong {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
